:"1185","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","Bradshaw, Lancashire, England":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, England","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"nl":{"1185–1235":"1185–1235","1190–1210":"1190–1210","1210–1234":"1210–1234","1160–1192":"1160–1192","1165–Female":"1165–Overleden","Aft. 1234":"na 1234","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","Bradshaw, Lancashire, England":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, England","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"en":{"1185–1235":"1185–1235","1190–1210":"1190–1210","1210–1234":"1210–1234","1160–1192":"1160–1192","1165–Female":"1165–Deceased","Aft. 1234":"after 1234","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","Bradshaw, Lancashire, England":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, England","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bradshaw","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of the three places called Bradshaw in Lancashire, Yorkshire, and Derbyshire, from Old English <i>brād</i> ‘broad’ + <i>sceaga</i> ‘thicket’."],"variants":[{"name":"Brayshaw","meanings":["English (Yorkshire): variant of   Bradshaw  , reflecting the local Yorkshire pronunciation."]}]},{"name":"Roger","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name, <i>Rog(i)er</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, from <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>gār</i>, <i>gēr</i> ‘spear’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain, replacing the native Old English form <i>Hrōðgār</i>. <i>Roger</i> was one of the most popular boys' names throughout the medieval period, but less so after the Reformation, though it has continued in regular use to the present day.  Roger, Count of Sicily  (  <i>c.</i>1031–1101 ), son of Tancred, recovered Sicily from the Arabs. His son, also called Roger, ruled Sicily as king, presiding over a court noted for its splendour and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":30,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":39,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Roger De Bradshaw was born in 1185, in Bradshaw, Lancashire, England, his father, Richard de Bradshagh, was 25 and his mother, N de Bradshagh, was 20. He had at least 1 daughter with Lady Alica Osbaldston. He died in 1235, in Standish, Lancashire, England, at the age of 50."},"et":{"1185–1235":"1185–1235","1190–1210":"1190–1210","1210–1234":"1210–1234","1160–1192":"1160–1192","1165–Female":"1165–Surnud","Aft. 1234":"pärast 1234","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","Bradshaw, Lancashire, England":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, England","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fi":{"1185–1235":"1185–1235","1190–1210":"1190–1210","1210–1234":"1210–1234","1160–1192":"1160–1192","1165–Female":"1165–Kuollut","Aft. 1234":"1234 jälkeen","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","Bradshaw, Lancashire, England":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, England","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England"},"fr":{"1185–1235":"1185–1235","1190–1210":"1190–1210","1210–1234":"1210–1234","1160–1192":"1160–1192","1165–Female":"1165–Décédée","Aft. 1234":"après 1234","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1224":"1224","1234":"1234","1210":"1210","1165":"1165","1185":"1185","1160":"1160","1192":"1192","Bradshaw, Lancashire, England":"Bradshaw, Lancashire, Angleterre","Standish, Lancashire, England":"Standish, Lancashire, Angleterre","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Roger De Bradshaw est né en 1185, à Bradshaw, Lancashire, Angleterre, son père, Richard de Bradshagh, avait 25 ans et sa mère, N de Bradshagh, avait 20 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Lady Alica Osbaldston. Il est décédé en 1235, à Standish, Lancashire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 50 ans."},"de":{"1185–1235":"1185–1235","1190–1210":"1190–1210","1210–1234":"1210–1234","1160–1192":"1160–1192","1165–Female":"1165–Verstorben","Aft. 1234":"nach 1234","1190":"1190","1215":"1215","12